cmux-linux — hardened, Linux-only clean fork
=============================================

This repository is a Linux Rust/GTK4 terminal for running AI coding agents,
derived from the cmux lineage. It is licensed under the GNU Affero General
Public License v3.0 or later (AGPL-3.0-or-later); see LICENSE. All derivative
work here remains under the same license.

Provenance
----------
  * manaflow-ai/cmux          — original cmux (macOS, Swift/AppKit). Upstream
                                concept and much of the surrounding tooling.
                                https://github.com/manaflow-ai/cmux
  * bradwilson331/cmux-linux  — first Rust/GTK4 Linux port (now unmaintained
                                and unbuildable).
  * tcsenpai/cmux-linux       — modernized, buildable Linux port; the direct
                                basis for this fork.
                                https://github.com/tcsenpai/cmux-linux

Thanks to all of the above. This fork would not exist without their work.

What this fork changes
----------------------
This is a cleanup + supply-chain-hardening fork, not new features:

  * Removed the macOS Swift app tree, Xcode project, marketing site, the
    accidentally-committed node_modules, internal planning dirs, and a
    committed debug log.
  * Submodules are pinned by commit (not floating branches) for reproducible
    builds — see .gitmodules.
  * The GLAD OpenGL loader is now compiled from source in build.rs
    (ghostty/vendor/glad) instead of linking a prebuilt object committed to
    the repo. Nothing opaque is linked into the binary.

Verified dependencies
---------------------
  * ghostty submodule is pinned to leeb003/ghostty@be9d18e9f — our own fork
    of tcsenpai/ghostty (branch cmux-fork-gtk4-platform), forked so the pin
    cannot disappear from under the build. Its delta over upstream
    manaflow-ai/ghostty is exactly 2 commits / 2 files / +44 −6
    (src/apprt/embedded.zig, src/renderer/OpenGL.zig) — a GTK4 embedded
    platform variant plus the OpenGL-loader fix. This patch was reviewed
    line by line and contains no network, file, or process activity.
  * agent-browser submodule is pinned to the upstream vercel-labs/agent-browser
    commit 328ce8a98 ("Pin Linux release glibc floor (#1417)").

Security posture
----------------
The Linux runtime contains no telemetry, analytics, crash reporting, or
auto-update, and makes no outbound network connections of its own. The
control surface is a per-user Unix domain socket (0600) under
$XDG_RUNTIME_DIR. The browser-preview feature downloads Google's official
Chrome for Testing into a per-user directory only when explicitly invoked.
